    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const dates  = $('Build Date Range').first().json;\nconst stats  = $('Get Shows Stats').first().json.data || {};\nconst shows  = $('Get Recent Shows').all();\nconst titles = shows.slice(0, 5).map(s => s.json.title || 'Untitled').join(', ');\n\nconst avgViewsPerShow = shows.length ? Math.round((stats.views ?? 0) / shows.length) : 0;\nconst viewToCartPct   = stats.views\n  ? (((stats.addToCartClicks ?? 0) / stats.views) * 100).toFixed(1)\n  : '0.0';\nconst cartToPurchasePct = stats.addToCartClicks\n  ? (((stats.purchases ?? 0) / stats.addToCartClicks) * 100).toFixed(1)\n  : '0.0';\nconst revenuePerViewer = stats.uniqueViewers\n  ? ((stats.revenue ?? 0) / stats.uniqueViewers).toFixed(2)\n  : '0.00';\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    from: dates.from,\n    to: dates.to,\n    title: `Weekly Live Shopping Report: ${dates.from} \u2192 ${dates.to}`,\n    prompt: `You are writing a weekly performance digest for a live shopping management team.\n\nPeriod: ${dates.from} \u2192 ${dates.to}\nShows Produced: ${shows.length}\nRecent Show Titles: ${titles || 'N/A'}\n\nAggregate Stats:\n- Total Views: ${stats.views ?? 0}\n- Unique Viewers: ${stats.uniqueViewers ?? 0}\n- Add-to-Cart Clicks: ${stats.addToCartClicks ?? 0}\n- Purchases: ${stats.purchases ?? 0}\n- Revenue: $${(stats.revenue ?? 0).toLocaleString()}\n\nDerived Metrics:\n- Avg Views Per Show: ${avgViewsPerShow}\n- View-to-Cart Rate: ${viewToCartPct}%\n- Cart-to-Purchase Rate: ${cartToPurchasePct}%\n- Revenue per Unique Viewer: $${revenuePerViewer}\n\nWrite a structured weekly analysis with these sections:\n\nPERFORMANCE SUMMARY\nOne paragraph overview of the week. Lead with the most significant result.\n\nCONVERSION FUNNEL ANALYSIS\nAnalyse the funnel from views to purchase. Identify where drop-off is highest and what it suggests about audience intent, product-show alignment, or presentation quality.\n\nHIGHLIGHTS\n3 specific positive observations, each with a brief data-backed reason.\n\nCONCERNS\n1-2 areas needing attention with concrete reasoning. Be direct.\n\nRECOMMENDATIONS\n3 actionable recommendations for next week. Tie each to a specific metric.\n\nOUTLOOK\nOne forward-looking sentence.\n\nRules: plain text only, section names in ALL CAPS on their own line, no markdown, no bullet symbols, professional tone.`\n  }\n}];"
      },
